    "What learning mode is more effective and preferred by college students for programming learning remains uncertain.",
    "This uncertainty is partly attributed to programming learning studies to date have been based on the comparison between the most commonly used technological sources and devices and traditional learning forms.",
    "As an illustrative instance, researchers have juxtaposed and contrasted various programming methodologies.",
    "Sun et al. (2021a), for instance, attempted to harmonize text-based programming techniques with isomorphic block-based techniques.",
    "With instructor-led delivery, Sun et al. (2021b) sought to reconcile learner-oriented, unplugged programming."
